                    <span>Author did a good job of explaining basic concepts of NAT, Firewalls, Load Balancer, Proxy Servers, Web servers. <P>Another aspect of this book is that, clear explanation of network equipment deployment issues, how it is being used.<BR> <BR>Finally, the advanced topic sections relating to each network element describes the concepts very clearly and by not getting into details of protocol message strucutures.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Wonderful</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
